Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) for thiophene + n-hexane at (338.15 and 323.15) K and thiophene  + 1-hexene at (333.15 and 323.15) K were measured with a circulation still. Maximum pressure azeotropes were  found in the thiophene + n-hexane system. Azeotropic behavior was not found for the thiophene + 1-hexene  system. The experimental results were correlated with Wilson model and also compared with original UNIFAC,  UNIFAC-Dortmund, and COSMO-RS predictive models. Analyses of liquid and vapor-phase composition were  determined with gas chromatograph and refractometer. All VLE measurements passed the three thermodynamic  consistency tests used.
Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium for Binary System of Thiophene + n-Hexane at (338.15 and 323.15) K and Thiophene + 1-Hexene at (333.15 and 323.15) K
